<DOC><DOCNO> SJMN91-06101062 </DOCNO><ACCESS> 06101062 </ACCESS><DESCRIPT>  SANTA-CRUZ; MAN; ARREST; DRUG; CRIME; SMUGGLING; ALASKA  </DESCRIPT><LEADPARA>  Alerted a year ago by state troopers in Alaska that a Santa Cruz resident hadshipped a suitcase containing three kilos of cocaine to the far northernstate, local drug agents began an investigation that has culminated in theman's arrest.;    Booked into jail in San Francisco on a federal warrant wasJohn Jerome King, 34, described by investigators as a distributor for a toolcompany. He was charged with interstate transportation of cocaine.  </LEADPARA><SECTION>  Local  </SECTION><HEADLINE>  SANTA CRUZ MAN HELD ON COCAINE CHARGES  </HEADLINE><TEXT>     The arrest warrant was issued in South Dakota, where King was also accusedof trafficking in the illegal drug, according to authorities.;    Ron Gravitt,supervising agent of the Santa Cruz County Narcotics Enforcement Team, saidKing was arrested last week at a gas station in Capitola. He was taken to SanFrancisco by federal marshals, who also participated in the arrest.;   According to Gravitt, state troopers in Alaska found the cocaine in a suitcaseat the Fairbanks airport. He said an investigation by the Alaska officers andNarcotics Enforcement Team officers indicated that the drugs had been shippedby King.;    Further investigation, which included analysis of handwritingsamples from the suspect, &quot;proved that King had purchased and filled out anovernight delivery receipt to send claim tickets for the suitcase to Alaska,&quot;Gravitt said in a prepared statement.;    An arrest warrant was obtained inSanta Clara County, Gravitt said. While awaiting an opportunity to make thearrest, agents learned of the arrest warrant from South Dakota.  </TEXT><BYLINE>  LEE QUARNSTROM, Mercury News Staff Writer  </BYLINE><COUNTRY>  USA  </COUNTRY><EDITION>  Santa Cruz/Monterey  </EDITION><CODE>  SJ  </CODE><NAME>  San Jose Mercury News  </NAME><PUBDATE>   910410  </PUBDATE> <DAY>  Wednesday  </DAY><MONTH>  April  </MONTH><PG.COL>  2B  </PG.COL><PUBYEAR>  1991  </PUBYEAR><REGION>  WEST  </REGION><STATE>  CA  </STATE><WORD.CT>  240  </WORD.CT><DATELINE>  Wednesday April 10, 199100101062,SJ1  </DATELINE><COPYRGHT>  Copyright 1991, San Jose Mercury News  </COPYRGHT><LIMLEN>  1  </LIMLEN><LANGUAGE>  ENG  </LANGUAGE></DOC>